1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:33,990 --> 00:01:36,990
All of you need to get off this island!

3
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:41,660
What do you mean, Sentomaru?!

4
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:45,500
What's happening on this island?!

5
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:49,340
Why did you deploy the pacifista
all over the island?!

6
00:01:52,130 --> 00:01:58,970
A long time ago, an island called Ohara
suddenly disappeared from the world map.

7
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:05,400
All because they defied the World Government.

8
00:02:08,650 --> 00:02:10,400
The Ohara Incident...

9
00:02:12,990 --> 00:02:17,120
On the island of Ohara, home to
the world's largest historical library...

10
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:23,460
scholars worked to decipher the poneglyphs,
an act forbidden by the government.

11
00:02:23,460 --> 00:02:25,500
In turn, the island's residents...

12
00:02:26,420 --> 00:02:30,960
were wiped out in a Marine bombardment.

13
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:34,840
The sole survivor of that incident...

14
00:02:36,010 --> 00:02:37,760
was Nico Robin.

15
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:46,900
If they're trying to kill Old Man Punk,
the smartest man in the world...

16
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,480
it means they considered the cost...

17
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:54,780
and still decided his head was worth the price.

18
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:02,750
If that's true, then something
even worse than Ohara...

19
00:03:02,750 --> 00:03:06,710
could be in store for this island!

20
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:17,340
Hurry, Straw Hat!

21
00:03:19,350 --> 00:03:22,470
What the hell is going on up there...?!

22
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:39,370
Shave!

23
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:05,430
Hand Pistol...

24
00:04:05,430 --> 00:04:06,930
Gum-Gum...

25
00:04:06,930 --> 00:04:08,190
...Yellow Lotus!

26
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:09,900
...Kong Organ!

27
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:26,000
Tempest Kick...

28
00:04:29,830 --> 00:04:30,960
Tumult!

29
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:35,880
White Thunder!

30
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:39,260
One-Sword Style Draw...

31
00:04:47,020 --> 00:04:49,890
Lethal Lion Song!

32
00:05:22,640 --> 00:05:23,640
Huh?!

33
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:25,930
Gimme a break, you jerks!

34
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:33,020
Quit getting up already!

35
00:05:33,020 --> 00:05:34,360
What are you, Kaido?!

36
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:37,070
Why don't our attacks work against them?!

37
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:38,940
Oh yeah...

38
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:44,490
They kinda remind me of that
King guy I fought in Wano.

39
00:05:45,370 --> 00:05:48,620
There was a lunarian on Kaido's crew?

40
00:05:48,620 --> 00:05:51,830
I didn't catch the name of his race...

41
00:05:52,210 --> 00:05:53,370
I see...

42
00:05:54,000 --> 00:06:00,760
That man is most likely the test subject who
escaped Punk Hazard with Kaido some time ago...

43
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:01,840
named Alber.

44
00:06:02,380 --> 00:06:04,590
The seraphim are indeed...

45
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:08,560
augmented with his lunarian blood.

46
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:10,640
So that's how it is, huh...?

47
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:14,980
In that case, keep your eyes
on those flames, guys!

48
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:19,030
Our attacks will only work when they go out.

49
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:22,990
When the fire's lit, they're practically invincible.

50
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:28,450
Sorry, I guess I wasted a bunch of our energy.

51
00:06:28,450 --> 00:06:31,790
I should have noticed sooner.

52
00:06:31,790 --> 00:06:35,420
Better late than never.
Now we know how to fight them.

53
00:06:35,420 --> 00:06:37,250
King's notable features were...

54
00:06:37,670 --> 00:06:38,460
white hair...

55
00:06:39,170 --> 00:06:40,630
dark skin...

56
00:06:41,340 --> 00:06:42,800
black wings...

57
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:45,180
and the flames on his back.

58
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:45,340
Pardon?!

59
00:06:45,340 --> 00:06:45,380
Pardon?!

60
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:45,430
Pardon?!

61
00:06:45,430 --> 00:06:45,680
Pardon?!

62
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:45,720
Pardon?!

63
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:45,760
Pardon?!

64
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:45,800
Pardon?!

65
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:46,050
Pardon?!

66
00:06:46,050 --> 00:06:46,090
Pardon?!

67
00:06:46,090 --> 00:06:46,140
Pardon?!

68
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:47,390
Pardon?!

69
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:45,800
What?!

70
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:46,050
What?!

71
00:06:46,050 --> 00:06:46,090
What?!

72
00:06:46,090 --> 00:06:46,140
What?!

73
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:47,390
What?!

74
00:06:46,090 --> 00:06:46,140
Huh?!

75
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:47,390
Huh?!

76
00:06:47,390 --> 00:06:50,470
– You should have noticed sooner!
– You should have noticed sooner!

77
00:06:54,270 --> 00:06:56,770
Hey! Where are you going, Helmet?

78
00:06:57,520 --> 00:07:01,730
I believe I know where Stella might be.

79
00:07:07,660 --> 00:07:08,620
Go!

80
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:11,910
Sorry for the trouble.

81
00:07:11,910 --> 00:07:13,370
Stay out of this!

82
00:07:13,370 --> 00:07:15,710
We're in a bit of a hurry!

83
00:07:25,170 --> 00:07:27,010
Let's go, Zeus!

84
00:07:27,010 --> 00:07:28,300
Yeah!

85
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:30,510
He's not a child!

86
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:34,180
He's hurting my friends!

87
00:07:34,180 --> 00:07:36,390
He nearly destroyed Edison!

88
00:07:36,730 --> 00:07:38,350
He's a killing machine!

89
00:07:41,110 --> 00:07:42,440
He's not cute!

90
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:44,320
He's not a child!

91
00:07:44,690 --> 00:07:45,990
That's right, Nami!

92
00:07:45,990 --> 00:07:47,320
Don't hesitate!

93
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:48,780
Shut your eyes if you have to!

94
00:07:48,780 --> 00:07:50,200
Just get me in there!

95
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:52,330
I'll take care of the rest!

96
00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:54,160
Thunderbolt!

97
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,460
Not enough!

98
00:08:00,670 --> 00:08:01,630
I've got you now!

99
00:08:13,140 --> 00:08:14,100
Bull's-eye!

100
00:08:17,980 --> 00:08:20,060
I'm sorry, Jinbe...

101
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,740
He dove down again!

102
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:27,990
Run!

103
00:08:30,870 --> 00:08:32,950
Nami, he's going to attack from below!

104
00:08:32,950 --> 00:08:33,660
What?!

105
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:38,830
It didn't work!

106
00:08:49,930 --> 00:08:52,640
Article 1 of the Sanjitution:

107
00:08:53,260 --> 00:08:55,930
The punishment for frightening Nami...

108
00:08:55,930 --> 00:08:56,850
is death!

109
00:09:00,350 --> 00:09:02,020
Aubad–

110
00:09:03,230 --> 00:09:06,480
Article 9 of the Sanjitution:

111
00:09:07,610 --> 00:09:10,860
The punishment for making Nami scream is a...

112
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:13,030
Raw Heat Strike!

113
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:26,250
Sanji!

114
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:28,260
Nami, did he hurt you?

115
00:09:28,260 --> 00:09:29,260
Are you alright?

116
00:09:29,260 --> 00:09:30,630
I'm fine, thanks!

117
00:09:30,630 --> 00:09:32,640
I'm glad to hear that.

118
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:34,640
I'll finish him off now.

119
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:38,060
I warned you, you little shit!

120
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:46,650
I don't care whether
you're a kid or even Jinbe...

121
00:09:47,570 --> 00:09:49,780
you get the death penalty either way.

122
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,530
Jinbe Junior!

123
00:09:53,910 --> 00:09:57,790
How dare you petrify York?!

124
00:09:57,790 --> 00:09:59,410
What should we do?!

125
00:10:01,790 --> 00:10:04,750
Hope you like the taste of this bubble gun!

126
00:10:08,670 --> 00:10:09,920
Hey!

127
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:11,380
It didn't work at all!

128
00:10:17,010 --> 00:10:18,220
What?!

129
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:21,140
You got sloppy!

130
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:29,730
The bubbles created by this gizmo
are loaded with the sea's energy!

131
00:10:30,110 --> 00:10:34,450
And that green blood gives you
the same weakness as those with powers!

132
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:37,780
Which means the bubbles tucker you out!

133
00:10:39,330 --> 00:10:41,330
That's awesome, Lilith!

134
00:10:41,330 --> 00:10:43,710
You're darn tootin'!

135
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,040
Alright!

136
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,920
Now's our chance to restrain her!

137
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:49,750
Leave it to me!

138
00:10:56,890 --> 00:10:58,600
Unhand me!

139
00:11:02,850 --> 00:11:03,980
Insolent brute!

140
00:11:03,980 --> 00:11:05,190
Know your place!

141
00:11:05,190 --> 00:11:07,690
It already wore off!

142
00:11:07,690 --> 00:11:09,940
That's because it only grazed her arm.

143
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:11,780
It should at least be stuck to her!

144
00:11:11,780 --> 00:11:13,690
You meanies! Jerks!

145
00:11:13,690 --> 00:11:15,780
Stupid dummies!

146
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:21,080
She's throwing a tantrum!

147
00:11:22,290 --> 00:11:24,960
It's a laser! We'd better skedaddle!

148
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,250
Y-Y-Yeah!

149
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:28,830
Run!

150
00:11:29,790 --> 00:11:32,300
S-Snake! Stand down!

151
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:34,880
You're just a seraphim! Don't be such a brat!

152
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:51,110
You're wide open!

153
00:11:56,450 --> 00:11:59,910
How do you like that, little punk?!

154
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,750
Good thinking, Franky!

155
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:07,500
Bubble guns sure are handy!

156
00:12:10,460 --> 00:12:12,710
Give it up, you runt!

157
00:12:14,210 --> 00:12:17,170
You're... You're hurting me...

158
00:12:19,130 --> 00:12:20,590
Sorry!

159
00:12:20,590 --> 00:12:23,510
Perfume Femur!

160
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:27,230
Crap! I'm turning to stone!

161
00:12:28,060 --> 00:12:29,940
Dammit!

162
00:12:31,650 --> 00:12:33,690
Franky got petrified!

163
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:34,860
This is bad!

164
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:36,400
He's gonna die!

165
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:41,530
Here she comes!

166
00:12:41,530 --> 00:12:42,240
Stop!

167
00:13:00,470 --> 00:13:03,300
Love-Love Mellow!

168
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:10,730
Usopp! Lilith!

169
00:13:25,530 --> 00:13:28,500
The only place Stella could possibly be...

170
00:13:28,870 --> 00:13:31,120
is in this room...

171
00:13:31,870 --> 00:13:32,960
What?

172
00:13:33,330 --> 00:13:34,960
Who are you?

173
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:37,800
Are you the one who did this to us?

174
00:13:38,210 --> 00:13:39,670
It can't be...

175
00:13:39,670 --> 00:13:41,800
You're the Cipher Pol agents from before!

176
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:42,760
Why are you here?!

177
00:13:43,260 --> 00:13:44,800
Help us...

178
00:13:45,430 --> 00:13:46,760
Please!

179
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:48,970
Get us out of here...

180
00:13:48,970 --> 00:13:50,520
I don't wanna die...

181
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:56,860
Stella!

182
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:03,450
So this is where you were!

183
00:14:05,030 --> 00:14:07,160
Who did this to you?!

184
00:14:07,830 --> 00:14:09,120
Shaka!

185
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:15,500
I'm glad you're okay!

186
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,000
I'll unlock the door!

187
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:17,920
Hey...

188
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,260
Shaka...

189
00:14:20,260 --> 00:14:22,050
Who's that with you?

190
00:14:22,050 --> 00:14:22,630
What?

191
00:14:39,980 --> 00:14:41,070
Shaka!

192
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:42,690
He's been shot!

193
00:14:42,690 --> 00:14:44,530
But why?!

194
00:15:11,180 --> 00:15:13,310
Stay vigilant, men.

195
00:15:13,310 --> 00:15:14,640
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

196
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:27,410
What?! Uncle Kizaru?!

197
00:15:27,410 --> 00:15:28,120
Yes...

198
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:33,790
He is on his way here with a fleet
of over a hundred vessels, large and small.

199
00:15:34,160 --> 00:15:36,000
Over a hundred?!

200
00:15:36,370 --> 00:15:41,460
CP0's mission is to eliminate
the doctor and wait for Kizaru's arrival.

201
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:44,800
So they're sending a Marine admiral...

202
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:47,550
They're taking this really seriously...

203
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:48,970
Indeed.

204
00:15:48,970 --> 00:15:51,310
They must see this as even worse than Ohara.

205
00:15:51,310 --> 00:15:52,680
Why?

206
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:53,810
Reason one:

207
00:15:53,810 --> 00:15:57,230
The doctor is carrying on
Ohara's forbidden research.

208
00:15:57,230 --> 00:16:00,360
More than that, he's making a lot of progress.

209
00:16:01,820 --> 00:16:02,940
And reason two:

210
00:16:02,940 --> 00:16:07,200
Unlike Ohara, Egghead
has the strength to fight back.

211
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,820
You mean the seraphim and
the army of pacifista?

212
00:16:11,450 --> 00:16:15,790
When you put it that way,
a full-force deployment makes sense.

213
00:16:15,790 --> 00:16:18,250
Let me know if anything happens!

214
00:16:18,620 --> 00:16:21,840
The Labophase's communication
systems are all down.

215
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:22,710
Got it.

216
00:16:26,300 --> 00:16:27,630
Did you get all that?!

217
00:16:27,630 --> 00:16:32,050
History tells us all we need to know about
what the Marines will do here!

218
00:16:32,050 --> 00:16:36,270
Are you saying that both we
and this facility will end up like Ohara?!

219
00:16:36,270 --> 00:16:37,390
Correct!

220
00:16:37,390 --> 00:16:39,390
You can't afford to hesitate now!

221
00:16:39,390 --> 00:16:42,150
Hurry up and evacuate Egghead!

222
00:16:42,150 --> 00:16:43,730
Go!

223
00:16:45,940 --> 00:16:47,110
Get the ships ready!

224
00:16:47,110 --> 00:16:48,860
We've gotta get off the island!

225
00:16:48,860 --> 00:16:50,860
Before the Marines get here!

226
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:52,820
Listen to Sentomaru!

227
00:16:53,620 --> 00:16:55,660
Usopp! Lilith!

228
00:16:55,660 --> 00:16:57,540
You little brat!

229
00:16:57,540 --> 00:16:59,120
Turn me back to normal!

230
00:17:01,250 --> 00:17:03,040
I got careless with my right side...

231
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:06,510
but my left is as strong as ever!

232
00:17:06,510 --> 00:17:10,630
Do you want a taste of my Weapons Left?!

233
00:17:10,630 --> 00:17:14,560
If you give up now, maybe I'll let you off...

234
00:17:17,810 --> 00:17:19,390
Um, I was just...

235
00:17:22,350 --> 00:17:24,820
Hey, get back here!

236
00:17:24,820 --> 00:17:27,190
Stop or I'll shoot!

237
00:17:27,780 --> 00:17:30,240
Why, S-Snake?!

238
00:17:30,650 --> 00:17:34,700
Who... Who's ordering you to do all this?!

239
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:38,370
Please, wait!

240
00:17:38,370 --> 00:17:40,370
Stop!

241
00:17:42,540 --> 00:17:43,920
Pythagoras!

242
00:17:50,920 --> 00:17:53,050
Wait! Hey!

243
00:17:53,050 --> 00:17:55,640
Wait, dammit!

244
00:18:02,310 --> 00:18:04,310
I hope everyone is okay...

245
00:18:04,310 --> 00:18:08,570
I keep hearing lots of screams and explosions.

246
00:18:08,570 --> 00:18:11,490
Well, we know the seraphim are on a rampage.

247
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:14,280
I just don't get it!

248
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:16,990
I thought the seraphim were on our side...

249
00:18:17,990 --> 00:18:21,370
Perhaps somebody overrode
their orders again.

250
00:18:23,120 --> 00:18:25,750
I'm worried about Nami and the others...

251
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:27,000
They'll be okay.

252
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:30,760
If Nami screams, a certain someone
will rush to her side in an instant.

253
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:31,970
Oh, that's true!

254
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:39,060
Anyone fighting will be stuck where they are.

255
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:44,520
Something could happen
to Vegapunk in the meantime.

256
00:18:44,520 --> 00:18:46,610
Good point! Let's hurry and find him!

257
00:18:46,610 --> 00:18:51,990
Come to think of it, there is
that old lab we sealed off...

258
00:18:51,990 --> 00:18:52,820
– What?
– What?

259
00:18:52,820 --> 00:18:56,280
I don't know why anyone
would go there, though...

260
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:57,530
Let's go check.

261
00:18:57,530 --> 00:19:01,450
We might be able to find a clue, at least.

262
00:19:01,450 --> 00:19:03,330
Lead the way, Atlas!

263
00:19:03,330 --> 00:19:04,370
You got it!

264
00:19:15,220 --> 00:19:16,890
Edison, stay with me!

265
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:19,350
Edison!

266
00:19:19,350 --> 00:19:24,560
Nami! I'll shed some weight
and go look for Vegapunk!

267
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:25,560
Okay!

268
00:19:32,570 --> 00:19:33,690
Oh no!

269
00:19:48,380 --> 00:19:50,840
Sanji, you're incredible!

270
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:56,430
Jinbe Junior...

271
00:19:56,430 --> 00:19:58,140
Do you even know...

272
00:19:58,140 --> 00:20:00,220
about the power of love?!

273
00:20:03,930 --> 00:20:06,810
Gum-Gum...

274
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:09,650
Red Hawk!

275
00:20:14,690 --> 00:20:19,700
Dammit! The flames on
their backs just won't go out!

276
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:26,660
Hey! The guy who looks like Hawk Eye ran off!

277
00:20:26,660 --> 00:20:28,120
Where'd he go?!

278
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:30,330
He must have changed his target priority.

279
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:31,040
Huh?

280
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:34,500
He's saving the tough ones for later
and going after the weaklings.

281
00:20:36,260 --> 00:20:41,340
Seeing their friends die also has the effect
of demoralizing the stronger opponents.

282
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:43,260
Luffy, I got this!

283
00:20:43,260 --> 00:20:44,260
I'll go after him!

284
00:20:44,260 --> 00:20:45,720
I'm counting on you, Zoro!

285
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:46,680
Oh, crap!

286
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:48,100
Hey, Usopp!

287
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:49,350
Go with him!

288
00:20:49,980 --> 00:20:52,610
He’s just gonna get lost!

289
00:20:52,610 --> 00:20:54,900
You're working me to the bone here!

290
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:57,110
Hold your horses, Roronoa!

291
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:59,820
Wait, who are you calling "Usopp"?!

292
00:21:09,830 --> 00:21:11,920
You're fighting me right now!

293
00:21:18,090 --> 00:21:19,880
Gum-Gum...

294
00:21:20,470 --> 00:21:22,840
Hawk Gatling!

295
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:24,810
Go out, fire!

296
00:21:25,180 --> 00:21:26,770
Idiot! Stop, Straw Hat!

297
00:21:26,770 --> 00:21:27,770
Use your head!

298
00:21:27,770 --> 00:21:30,980
You'll never beat him that way!

299
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:41,700
This has been the whole story of what happened
the day before the infamous Egghead Incident...

300
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:46,620
However, the story truly begins
three months prior...

301
00:21:48,660 --> 00:21:50,580
The Holy Land, Mary Geoise.

302
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:54,080
...is...

303
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:55,130
...g... ...d...

304
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:59,300
This is E... ...d...

305
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:00,590
I can't hear you!

306
00:22:02,010 --> 00:22:04,640
This is Egghe... ...d...

307
00:22:04,640 --> 00:22:06,720
I need to talk to... ...igher-ups.

308
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:08,220
What business do you have?

309
00:22:08,970 --> 00:22:10,980
...need to talk to the higher-ups...

310
00:22:10,980 --> 00:22:12,440
I said state your business!

311
00:22:13,690 --> 00:22:15,810
Dr. Vegapunk is...

312
00:22:15,810 --> 00:22:18,940
researching the Void Century.

313
00:22:31,620 --> 00:22:39,000
After receiving that tip, CP5 was dispatched
to Egghead to verify the truth...

314
00:22:39,670 --> 00:22:41,840
but came up empty handed.

315
00:22:42,260 --> 00:22:44,840
With their investigation
complete, they set sail...

316
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:47,970
only for their ship to vanish without a trace.

317
00:22:55,190 --> 00:22:57,400
To investigate the disappearance,

318
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:03,110
more agents from CP7, then CP8,
were dispatched to Egghead...

319
00:23:03,110 --> 00:23:06,820
but not one returned to the government.

320
00:23:08,700 --> 00:23:10,950
This is Egghead.

321
00:23:10,950 --> 00:23:13,540
Put me through to the higher-ups.

322
00:23:24,050 --> 00:23:28,390
After a meeting between the Five Elders
and this mysterious figure...

323
00:23:28,390 --> 00:23:32,470
the genius scientist's betrayal
of researching the Void Century...

324
00:23:32,930 --> 00:23:34,680
was made abundantly clear.

325
00:23:36,770 --> 00:23:40,980
The Five Elders decided that Vegapunk
would be assassinated.

326
00:23:43,740 --> 00:23:48,280
Cipher Pol Aigis 0 was tasked
with carrying out the mission and set sail.

327
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:53,620
However, the Five Elders expected
resistance from Vegapunk,

328
00:23:53,620 --> 00:23:56,040
and decided to oversee matters personally.

329
00:23:56,040 --> 00:24:00,170
Admiral Kizaru was chosen as an escort.

330
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:11,600
Additionally, a request for reinforcements
was sent to various Marine branches.

331
00:24:15,850 --> 00:24:20,610
The deployment was as if
they were preparing for war.

332
00:24:35,540 --> 00:24:38,500
However, an unexpected guest arrived...

333
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:43,460
the ship of Emperor Straw Hat Luffy.

334
00:24:54,810 --> 00:25:00,850
The government chafed at
the intruders' unforeseen arrival.

335
00:25:00,850 --> 00:25:02,110
See?!

336
00:25:02,860 --> 00:25:06,190
Things are getting complicated again!

337
00:25:10,910 --> 00:25:12,570
Them again?!

338
00:25:14,450 --> 00:25:16,080
Regardless...

339
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:18,910
this incident will conclude tomorrow...

340
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:25,130
and its outcome will shock
the world like nothing before.

341
00:25:29,340 --> 00:25:30,430
Hey!

342
00:25:30,430 --> 00:25:33,180
Are you responsible for all of this?!

343
00:25:33,180 --> 00:25:34,140
Answer me!

344
00:26:07,670 --> 00:26:09,880
Why would you do this...

345
00:26:12,090 --> 00:26:13,220
York?!

346
00:26:19,020 --> 00:26:20,890
Guess what, Stella!

347
00:26:20,890 --> 00:26:23,980
I'm gonna be a Celestial Dragon!

348
00:26:25,940 --> 00:26:28,190
What are you talking about, York?!

349
00:26:28,190 --> 00:26:30,690
You've been to Mary Geoise, right?!

350
00:26:30,690 --> 00:26:33,820
Do you really want to be
one of those vile people?!

351
00:26:34,950 --> 00:26:36,910
That's something Shaka would say.

352
00:26:37,530 --> 00:26:40,040
But he's dead now!

353
00:26:42,330 --> 00:26:44,120
It's too complicated.

354
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:45,750
We're all Vegapunk.

355
00:26:47,460 --> 00:26:50,300
Does the world really need…

356
00:26:52,510 --> 00:26:54,760
more than one Vegapunk?

